meanings.definition: Not able to be determined or decided
meanings.sent1: The outcome of the game was indeterminable until the final whistle.
meanings.sent2: The color of the sky at sunset was indeterminable, changing from pink to orange.
meanings.sent3: It was indeterminable whether the cat or the dog made the mess in the living room.
meanings.sent4: The path through the forest was indeterminable, twisting and turning unpredictably.
meanings.sent5: The taste of the exotic fruit was indeterminable, a mix of sweet and sour flavors.

meanings.definition: Unable to be accurately measured or calculated
meanings.sent1: The exact weight of the ancient artifact was indeterminable due to its fragile state.
meanings.sent2: The distance to the nearest star was indeterminable with the telescope they had.
meanings.sent3: The number of bubbles in the fizzy drink was indeterminable, popping at different rates.
meanings.sent4: Her emotions were indeterminable, a whirlwind of conflicting feelings.
meanings.sent5: The value of the antique vase was indeterminable, with experts giving varying estimates.
